\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\int\delta^{2}f\mathcal{F}[f]=\int d^{2}\boldsymbol{\alpha}\mathcal{F}(\boldsymbol{\alpha})
\]

\end_inset

If the basis contains an infinite number of modes, the integral is treated
 as a limit 
